Custom Installations

Steps
1.	Create a user cpeadmin and its group as p8admin
sudo useradd -m -s /bin/bash cpeadmin
sudo passwd cpeadmin
sudo groupadd p8admin
sudo usermod -g p8admin cpeadmin
2.	Change owner for /lotus
chown -R cpeadmin:p8admin /lotus
3.	Login as cpeadmin and create directory /lotus/ds1/IBM
su – cpeadmin
mkdir /lotus/ds1/IBM or mkdir /lotus/data01/IBM
4.	Login as root and create a link for /opt/IBM to /lotus/ds1/IBM. 
cd /opt
ln -s /lotus/ds1/IBM IBM or ln -s /lotus/data01/IBM IBM
chown -h cpeadmin:p8admin /opt/IBM
chmod 777 /opt/IBM
5.	Login as cpeadmin and create a directory for all the binaries
su - cpeadmin
mkdir /home/cpeadmin/Softwares
chmod 777 /home/cpeadmin/Softwares
chmod 777 /home/cpeadmin
6.	Copy all binaries to /home/cpeadmin/Softwares/ 
Assign owner as cpeadmin, assign group as p8admin and assign permissions 777 to the binaries
